  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">While at Mrs. Maria W. Chapman&apos;s house, Deborah Weston learned that &quot;Mr. Smith of Bowdoin College&quot; had made a long call and that &quot;they talked metaphysicks [sic] &amp; admired one another.&quot; Tilson [Joseph Tilson?] is keeping &quot;the office [of the Mass. Anti-Slavery Society] &amp; very grand he is.&quot; Deborah attended the monthly concert [a concert of prayer for the slaves] with Lucinda Otis and Ann Greene Chapman. Brother [William S.?] Porter prayed that the slaves in the South might not be tempted to rise and join the Indians. Porter stated that the Presbyterian synod at Pittsburgh had chosen a slaveholder as president. Deborah fears that the Boston Female Anti-Slavery Society will not be able to find a church in which to hold their meeting.</subfield>
